28/02/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The ethnic Hungarian Democratic Alliance of Hungarians (UDMR), part of the ruling coalition, elected Kelemen Hunor as its new leader at a congress Saturday (February 26th). He assured that the UDMR will not leave the ruling coalition and said he would continue the policy of co-operation with the senior ruling Liberal Democratic Party. Hunor, the culture minister, is an ally of the former head of the party, Marko Bela. (Hotnews.ro, Evenimentul Zilei, Ziare, Realitatea - 26/02/11)
